<!-- Complete Code Structure -->
<div>
<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Complete Arduino Code:</h4>
<div class="bg-gray-900 text-green-400 p-4 rounded-lg text-xs font-mono
overflow-x-auto max-h-80 overflow-y-auto">
<div class="space-y-1">
<div><span class="text-orange-400">// Blynk Template
Configuration</span></div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">#define</span> <span class="text-yellow-
400">BLYNK_TEMPLATE_ID</span> <span class="text-green-300">"TMPL3cb2LRu6D"</span></div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">#define</span> <span class="text-yellow-
400">BLYNK_TEMPLATE_NAME</span> <span class="text-green-300">"Home
Automation"</span></div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">#define</span> <span class="text-yellow-
400">BLYNK_AUTH_TOKEN</span> <span class="text-green-
300">"W3FQPpoNHpI452tnihoqEEoEQ2tSaT8v"</span></div>
<div class="mt-2"></div>
<div><span class="text-orange-400">// Library Includes</span></div>
<div><span class="text-purple-400">#include</span> <span class="text-
green-300">&lt;ESP8266WiFi.h&gt;</span></div>
<div><span class="text-purple-400">#include</span> <span class="text-
green-300">&lt;BlynkSimpleEsp8266.h&gt;</span></div>
<div class="mt-2"></div>
<div><span class="text-orange-400">// WiFi Credentials</span></div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">#define</span> <span class="text-yellow-
400">PASS_LENGTH</span> <span class="text-white">8</span></div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">#define</span> <span class="text-yellow-
400">WIFI_SSID</span> <span class="text-green-300">"Samsung"</span></div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">#define</span> <span class="text-yellow-
400">WIFI_PASSWORD</span> <span class="text-green-300">"sannutha"</span></div>
<div class="mt-2"></div>
<div><span class="text-orange-400">// Global Variables</span></div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">char</span> auth[] = <span class="text-
yellow-400">BLYNK_AUTH_TOKEN</span>;</div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">char</span> ssid[] = <span class="text-
yellow-400">WIFI_SSID</span>;</div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">char</span> pass[] = <span class="text-
yellow-400">WIFI_PASSWORD</span>;</div>
<div class="mt-2"></div>
<div><span class="text-orange-400">// Relay Pin
Configuration</span></div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">int</span> relaypin1 = <span class="text-
yellow-400">D1</span>;</div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">int</span> relaypin2 = <span class="text-
yellow-400">D2</span>;</div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">int</span> relaypin3 = <span class="text-
yellow-400">D3</span>;</div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">int</span> relaypin4 = <span class="text-
yellow-400">D4</span>;</div>
<div class="mt-2"></div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">void</span> <span class="text-yellow-
400">setup</span>() {</div>
<div class="ml-4">Serial.<span class="text-yellow-400">begin</span>(<span
class="text-white">115200</span>);</div>
<div class="ml-4">WiFi.<span class="text-yellow-400">begin</span>(ssid,
pass);</div>
<div class="ml-4"><span class="text-blue-400">while</span> (WiFi.<span
class="text-yellow-400">status</span>() != <span class="text-yellow-400">WL_CONNECTED</span>)
{</div>
<div class="ml-8"><span class="text-yellow-400">delay</span>(<span
class="text-white">1000</span>);</div>
<div class="ml-8">Serial.<span class="text-yellow-
400">println</span>(<span class="text-green-300">"Connecting to WiFi..."</span>);</div>
<div class="ml-4">}</div>
<div class="ml-4">Serial.<span class="text-yellow-
400">println</span>(<span class="text-green-300">"Connected to WiFi"</span>);</div>
<div class="ml-4">Blynk.<span class="text-yellow-400">begin</span>(auth,
ssid, pass);</div>
<div class="ml-4"><span class="text-yellow-
400">pinMode</span>(relaypin1, <span class="text-yellow-400">OUTPUT</span>);</div>
<div class="ml-4"><span class="text-yellow-
400">pinMode</span>(relaypin2, <span class="text-yellow-400">OUTPUT</span>);</div>
<div class="ml-4"><span class="text-yellow-
400">pinMode</span>(relaypin3, <span class="text-yellow-400">OUTPUT</span>);</div>
<div class="ml-4"><span class="text-yellow-
400">pinMode</span>(relaypin4, <span class="text-yellow-400">OUTPUT</span>);</div>
<div class="ml-4"><span class="text-yellow-
400">digitalWrite</span>(relaypin1, <span class="text-yellow-400">HIGH</span>); <span
class="text-orange-400">// Initialize relay pins</span></div>
<div class="ml-4"><span class="text-yellow-
400">digitalWrite</span>(relaypin2, <span class="text-yellow-400">HIGH</span>);</div>
<div class="ml-4"><span class="text-yellow-
400">digitalWrite</span>(relaypin3, <span class="text-yellow-400">HIGH</span>);</div>
<div class="ml-4"><span class="text-yellow-
400">digitalWrite</span>(relaypin4, <span class="text-yellow-400">HIGH</span>);</div>
<div>}</div>
<div class="mt-2"></div>
<div><span class="text-blue-400">void</span> <span class="text-yellow-
400">loop</span>() {</div>
<div class="ml-4">Blynk.<span class="text-yellow-400">run</span>();</div>
<div class="ml-4"><span class="text-yellow-400">delay</span>(<span
class="text-white">50</span>); <span class="text-orange-400">// Add delay between Blynk.run()
calls</span></div>
<div>}</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
Designed and implemented an ultra-energy efficient reversible Quantum-dot
Cellular Automata (QCA) 8 to 1 multiplexer using advanced quantum computing principles. This
project focuses on nanotechnology applications and energy optimization at the quantum level.
</p>

<span class="bg-orange-100 text-orange-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-

<span class="bg-red-100 text-red-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-

<!-- CMOS vs QCA Performance Analysis -->
<div>
<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">CMOS vs QCA Performance
Analysis:</h4>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-4">
<!-- CMOS Limitations -->
<div class="bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-red-400">
<div class="font-medium text-red-800 text-sm mb-2">CMOS Design
Limitations:</div>
<ul class="space-y-1 text-xs text-red-600">
<li>• Substantial on-chip power consumption escalation</li>
<li>• Limited scalability due to increased I/O usage</li>
<li>• High DSP48 utilization requirements</li>
<li>• Inconsistent delay values affecting reliability</li>
<li>• Reduced efficiency in high-performance applications</li>
</ul>
</div>
<!-- QCA Advantages -->
<div class="bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-green-400">
<div class="font-medium text-green-800 text-sm mb-2">Proposed QCA
Improvements:</div>
<ul class="space-y-1 text-xs text-green-600">
<li>• Lower on-chip power consumption</li>
<li>• Improved scalability and reduced I/O requirements</li>
<li>• Enhanced reliability with consistent performance</li>
<li>• Increased fan-out capabilities</li>
<li>• Superior efficiency for modern applications</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<!-- Research Conclusion -->
<div>
<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Research Conclusion:</h4>
<div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-purple-50 p-4 rounded-lg border
border-blue-200">
<p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
The existing CMOS design exhibits significant performance drawbacks,
including substantial escalation in on-chip power consumption, limited scalability due to increased
I/O usage and DSP48 utilization, and inconsistent delay values. These limitations hinder the design's
efficiency, reliability, and overall performance, making it less suitable for modern high-performance
applications.
</p>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
In contrast, the proposed QCA system demonstrates notable
improvements, achieving lower on-chip power consumption, improved scalability, enhanced
reliability, and increased fan-out. These advancements showcase the proposed QCA system's ability
to overcome the existing CMOS design's limitations, offering a more efficient, scalable, and reliable
solution.
</p>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
The proposed QCA system's superior performance makes it an attractive
alternative for high-performance applications, such as computing, networking, and data storage.
Furthermore, the improved performance, scalability, and reliability make it an ideal candidate for
emerging technologies like artificial intelligence, Internet of Things (IoT), and 5G networks.
</p>
</div>
</div>

// Smooth scrolling for navigation links
document.querySelectorAll('a[href^="#"]').forEach(anchor => {
anchor.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
e.preventDefault();
const target = document.querySelector(this.getAttribute('href'));
if (target) {
target.scrollIntoView({
behavior: 'smooth',
block: 'start'
});
}
});
});
// Mobile menu toggle
const mobileMenuBtn = document.getElementById('mobile-menu-btn');
const nav = document.querySelector('nav');
mobileMenuBtn.addEventListener('click', function() {
// Simple mobile menu implementation
const navLinks = nav.querySelector('.hidden.md\\:flex');
if (navLinks.classList.contains('hidden')) {
navLinks.classList.remove('hidden');
navLinks.classList.add('flex', 'flex-col', 'absolute', 'top-full', 'left-0', 'w-full', 'bg-white',
'shadow-lg', 'p-4');
} else {
navLinks.classList.add('hidden');
navLinks.classList.remove('flex', 'flex-col', 'absolute', 'top-full', 'left-0', 'w-full', 'bg-white',
'shadow-lg', 'p-4');
}
});
// Fade in animation on scroll
const observerOptions = {
threshold: 0.1,
rootMargin: '0px 0px -50px 0px'
};
const observer = new IntersectionObserver(function(entries) {
entries.forEach(entry => {
if (entry.isIntersecting) {
entry.target.style.animationDelay = '0.2s';
entry.target.classList.add('fade-in');
}
});
}, observerOptions);
// Observe all sections
document.querySelectorAll('section > div').forEach(section => {
observer.observe(section);
});
// Typing animation for hero text
const typingText = document.querySelector('.typing-animation');
if (typingText) {
const text = 'Sannutha Eluru';
let index = 0;
function typeWriter() {
if (index < text.length) {
typingText.textContent = text.slice(0, index + 1);
index++;
setTimeout(typeWriter, 100);
}
}
setTimeout(typeWriter, 1000);
}
// Project details toggle functionality
function toggleProjectDetails(projectId) {
const detailsElement = document.getElementById(projectId + '-details');
const button = event.target.closest('button');
const toggleText = button.querySelector('.project-toggle-text');
const toggleIcon = button.querySelector('.project-toggle-icon');
if (detailsElement.classList.contains('hidden')) {
detailsElement.classList.remove('hidden');
toggleText.textContent = 'Hide Details';
toggleIcon.style.transform = 'rotate(180deg)';
} else {
detailsElement.classList.add('hidden');
toggleText.textContent = 'View Details';
toggleIcon.style.transform = 'rotate(0deg)';
}
}
